annotation.TEXT: Well, it looks like I can use my athleticism (or maybe this cannon, if I wasn't so athletic) to jump over the wall to the left...
I could backtrack to the left now, but... Nah. (If there was something good that I missed there, let me know!)
Hmm... Do I want the athletic peach? ...Yeah, probably.
Yep, just as I was told. Also, there's that "TL" again. Doesn't that stand for "Translator's" or "Translation"? If so, there's enough room to spell it out.
Okay, that opens up Fantomu Mura. Now, Haru Mori took me a decent amount of time to complete, so I'm going to stop here.
Yes, the goal! And, it's the secret exit! (Yeah, it darn well better be the secret exit, after what I went through to get here!)
Alright, time for new stuff. Instead of going down into the water there, I'll keep heading right.
Multiple coins, which I'm messing up on...
So, next time, I could head to either Fantomu Mura, Yukkuri Take, Rainy Clouds, or Walljump Xtrem DX *. Place your votes for where you want me to go next!
Okay, not bad. It's gonna take some effort to get my average back above 35, though.
Yep, this isn't one of those blocks that gives you a guaranteed feather, so no double jumping for me right now.
So, apparently, "Haru Mori" means "Spring Forest"...
Alright, I'm going to "L" here to stop the snake's fireballs for a moment.
I wonder if I'm missing anything good on the top route here... Meh, I don't really care that much right now, unless there's something like a moon up there.
Moon count: 1

Oh, cool. As I'm typing this right now, the people finally got Totodile to evolve into Croconaw at level 29! Interestingly enough, it could potentially evolve again next level into Feraligatr, if the people allow it!
Whoa! They just came out of the trees, man.
That unlocks Yukkuri Take, and I already know what a Yukkuri is. Now, let's go back for the normal exit in Haru Mori.
There's the goal, with a snake behind it. Ooh, I can use the snake's fireballs to help me out here!
Oh, cool. I can destroy those undead hopping guys (I think they're called "Pionpi") with a spin jump.
I wonder if the people will ever allow AJDNNW's Totodile to evolve... It's now at level 28 as I'm typing this, and still keeps being denied evolution (Totodile normally evolves at level 18).
MOON!!! ...AND, OMG!!! THERE WERE EVEN MORE MOONS UP THERE!!!
I got 29 coins from the lower block, which is decent.
Ah, good. A peach. Now I'm going to backtrack a bit...
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! Where am I headed next? Let's find out...
I must've missed something somewhere...
Okay, fortunately, I didn't die a terrible, terrible death there.
I'd better use this one to reach the ? block.
Ha! I gotta make sure I spin jump on the snakes so that they don't respawn.
Whoa, cannon.
Nuts! And I got hit again immediately! I hate flying cheepos, especially with how frequently they've appeared in New Strange Mario Bros.! Okay, let's try not to die here...
Whoa! That came dangerously close to burninating the extreme corner of my cap!
Whoa. Okay, that snake's totally unreachable, and this fried fish combo meal is going to be tricky to get past.
There's probably something good in that underwater passage there. However, I'd better stomp that flower first.
Ack! That fireball managed to make the extreme corner of my cap feel the power of toasty.
Oh, hey. We've got some other SML enemies here too!
Goal tape average so far: 708 / 21 = 33.714 stars each.
So, Haru Mori it is! (I keep wanting to type "Tori" instead of "Mori", and then correcting myself. If I left any of them as "Tori", I'm sure you guys will be more than happy to point it out!)
Yeah, I wasn't going to put much effort into trying for a high star total here. I needed 30 for the bonus game, and I doubt I could possibly get that much from the ground while small.
BGM: CUSTOM - Ievan Polkka
Whoa, almost felt the power of toasty there.
Oh, I recognize those guys from Super Mario Land. They're flammable/inflammable, but if you stomp them instead, they'll wake up again after a few seconds, kind of like Dry Bones.
I've decided not to speed up the footage here, because it's likely going to be a different experience starting off this level small.
Whoops, didn't mean to hit that again.
Yep, it's stompable, just like in SML. Wait, why did those snakes respawn? Didn't I just stomp them?
At least I can spin jump off of the snakes' fireballs.
BGM: Sexy Parodius - Lovely Otohmia (also known as Miyam Miyam)
A pipe! Get me outta here!
Capitalize "Japanese" and "Google" here.
I gotta remember I can wall jump with the peach's power as well.
Nothing up there aside from a ceiling way up in the trees.
1-ups scored this time: 7.69 Bonus game average so far: 40.00 / 6 = 6.66667 1-ups each. (It's interesting how my total is exactly 40 now!)
Ooh, peachy. And, I think I can keep going left...
Now there's buried flowers that I can't do anything about, but their attacks aren't difficult to avoid.
More unreachable buried snakes. This is gonna be a thing for the rest of the level now, isn't it?
And the snake respawned again! What if I destroy it with a spin jump?
"R", matey!
Oh, what? The bottom of this tree must be obscuring a solid platform. I'm gonna have to come out of the water for a second here.
Huh. I wonder how I'm supposed to reach that midpoint?
BGM: Pok√©mon Gold/Silver/Crystal - Game Corner
Okay, I should be relatively safe if I stay near the bottom center of the screen and move slowly. I'll just let any Pionpis jump out of bounds if possible...

What the heck? Okay, I have no idea why I got hurt there. It wasn't shooting a fireball at that moment, and I was descending (and stomped it immediately after shrinking). Maybe it's a glitch with that custom sprite. Unfortunately, that unfair hit denies me a better power up from this block.
And, more multiple coins, which I'm not messing up on this time.
By the way, at the end of the previous episode, Rumia had 10 possible outs out of the 44 cards remaining in the deck, so Rumia's chance of winning was 10/44, or about 22.7%.
I want to see if that flower there is stompable. But, maybe I should get rid of the snake first.
Blue shell = Walljump Xtrem DX *. Red shell = Haru Mori.
Also, sorry, but I couldn't think of any good Reimu Hakurei impressions to make.
Goal tape average so far: 748 / 22 = 34 stars each.

Yeah, I have no idea how to reach that midpoint. Oh, well. Let's forget it for now. (Actually, thinking about it now, there's a path I didn't check that was on the way to the secret exit, which could lead to the midpoint.)

In the meantime, I'll just sit on Kabu Katakomb and... Aw, what's this? I can't look around the map by pressing Start in this hack, so I can't do that jittery thing to end the video like I often did in Super Marina World. Oh, well. To be continued...
I wonder where this pipe leads...

Yeah, they stay dead when spin jumped on, but shouldn't normal stomping them kill them for good as well? Maybe that's a glitch with that particular custom sprite, where it's not considered "dead" by the game, and can still respawn.
Red shell wins!
